I'm going to put him in traction
and put him back together.

00:10:35.350 --> 00:10:38.206 align:middle line:90%
[BEEPING]

00:10:38.206 --> 00:10:41.070 align:middle line:90%


00:10:41.070 --> 00:10:44.940 align:middle line:84%
I would go out for years
after the car accident.

00:10:44.940 --> 00:10:48.140 align:middle line:84%
And people would say, hey, how'd
you get that scar on your face.

00:10:48.140 --> 00:10:50.540 align:middle line:84%
Or it would be like I'd
be out at some place,

00:10:50.540 --> 00:10:53.063 align:middle line:84%
or even, I'll never
forget it, some woman

00:10:53.063 --> 00:10:54.230 align:middle line:90%
came up to me at a bar once.

00:10:54.230 --> 00:10:55.740 align:middle line:84%
She said, what
happened to your face?

00:10:55.740 --> 00:10:56.540 align:middle line:90%
You know?

00:10:56.540 --> 00:10:58.332 align:middle line:84%
And people-- and I
meet them all time,

00:10:58.332 --> 00:10:59.540 align:middle line:90%
people who have facial scars.

00:10:59.540 --> 00:11:02.090 align:middle line:84%
It's very traumatizing
because, you know,

00:11:02.090 --> 00:11:03.595 align:middle line:90%
that's your facade to the world.

00:11:03.595 --> 00:11:04.970 align:middle line:84%
You're like, this
is your person.

00:11:04.970 --> 00:11:08.810 align:middle line:84%
And mine was-- it took
five different surgeries

00:11:08.810 --> 00:11:12.260 align:middle line:84%
to put it back together so that
I have some kind of semblance

00:11:12.260 --> 00:11:14.720 align:middle line:90%
of a normal smile.

00:11:14.720 --> 00:11:18.020 align:middle line:84%
For 25 years, I had
this vengeance fantasy

00:11:18.020 --> 00:11:22.400 align:middle line:84%
of going to find this driver
and doing to his face what

00:11:22.400 --> 00:11:23.600 align:middle line:90%
happened to mine.

00:11:23.600 --> 00:11:25.940 align:middle line:84%
And I would find myself
in the middle of the night

00:11:25.940 --> 00:11:28.160 align:middle line:84%
sometimes just having
these horrible, you know,

00:11:28.160 --> 00:11:31.850 align:middle line:84%
like the world is unjust, and
this whole terrible thing.

00:11:31.850 --> 00:11:33.920 align:middle line:84%
Fred Luskin, who wrote
"Forgive For Good",

00:11:33.920 --> 00:11:36.920 align:middle line:84%
he was speaking
about these topics.

00:11:36.920 --> 00:11:41.030 align:middle line:84%
So one night, I wrote a letter
to the driver of the car.

00:11:41.030 --> 00:11:42.290 align:middle line:90%
And I just put it away.

00:11:42.290 --> 00:11:43.910 align:middle line:84%
I didn't mean to
send it or anything.

00:11:43.910 --> 00:11:46.450 align:middle line:84%
And then I woke up the next
morning, and I read it.

00:11:46.450 --> 00:11:49.700 align:middle line:84%
And I was just like let me check
out what's on the internet.

00:11:49.700 --> 00:11:53.240 align:middle line:84%
So I googled him and
found them on Facebook.

00:11:53.240 --> 00:11:56.530 align:middle line:84%
And I set up a second
Ira Israel account

00:11:56.530 --> 00:11:58.190 align:middle line:84%
so he would see
it's me, but I just

00:11:58.190 --> 00:12:00.620 align:middle line:84%
didn't want him to see my
whole life or anything.

00:12:00.620 --> 00:12:05.030 align:middle line:90%
And I sent the letter.

00:12:05.030 --> 00:12:08.220 align:middle line:84%
You know, I just told them what
I'd done for those 25 years.

00:12:08.220 --> 00:12:11.770 align:middle line:84%
And you know, things I
was feeling and whatnot.

00:12:11.770 --> 00:12:12.570 align:middle line:90%
And I went to work.

00:12:12.570 --> 00:12:15.520 align:middle line:90%
And I came home.

00:12:15.520 --> 00:12:17.870 align:middle line:84%
It was probably
like 6:00 at night.

00:12:17.870 --> 00:12:21.000 align:middle line:84%
And I was like, OK, let me check
this other Facebook account.

00:12:21.000 --> 00:12:24.120 align:middle line:84%
And lo and behold, I received
an equally long letter.

00:12:24.120 --> 00:12:25.870 align:middle line:90%
And I started to read it.

00:12:25.870 --> 00:12:28.930 align:middle line:90%
And it was really heartfelt.

00:12:28.930 --> 00:12:35.100 align:middle line:84%
And it's surprising
to everybody when

00:12:35.100 --> 00:12:37.230 align:middle line:84%
you show up in a certain
way, like I can't

00:12:37.230 --> 00:12:39.660 align:middle line:90%
tell you be vulnerable, right?

00:12:39.660 --> 00:12:42.300 align:middle line:84%
But if I show up
in a certain way,

00:12:42.300 --> 00:12:45.360 align:middle line:90%
I can inspire you or enroll you.

00:12:45.360 --> 00:12:49.020 align:middle line:84%
So I don't know how much
personal work this person

00:12:49.020 --> 00:12:51.300 align:middle line:84%
had done over the past
25 years or something.

00:12:51.300 --> 00:12:55.620 align:middle line:84%
But he showed up
like a gentleman.

00:12:55.620 --> 00:13:01.540 align:middle line:84%
And we went back and forth for
a week, talking about our lives.

00:13:01.540 --> 00:13:15.260 align:middle line:84%
And at the end of the week, he
had told me how sorry he was.

00:13:15.260 --> 00:13:20.260 align:middle line:84%
And for some reason,
I just felt compelled.

00:13:20.260 --> 00:13:22.160 align:middle line:84%
And I just wrote
in all capitals,

00:13:22.160 --> 00:13:26.720 align:middle line:84%
if it helps you in any
way, I forgive you.

00:13:26.720 --> 00:13:29.990 align:middle line:90%
And I deleted the account.

00:13:29.990 --> 00:13:33.320 align:middle line:84%
And I never had any of those
machinations or anything,

00:13:33.320 --> 00:13:35.560 align:middle line:84%
like, all the
negativity, you know?

00:13:35.560 --> 00:13:39.860 align:middle line:84%
And that's why I talk about this
irony cause your mind was built

00:13:39.860 --> 00:13:42.890 align:middle line:84%
to create resentments-- woulda,
coulda, shoulda, didn't.

00:13:42.890 --> 00:13:47.510 align:middle line:84%
And those are the
things that show up

00:13:47.510 --> 00:13:51.110 align:middle line:84%
as the causes of suffering
because, you know,

00:13:51.110 --> 00:13:53.120 align:middle line:84%
you're trying to change
the unchangeable.

00:13:53.120 --> 00:13:57.050 align:middle line:90%
I can't go back to 1985.

00:13:57.050 --> 00:14:01.300 align:middle line:84%
And if I did, something worse
might have happened, right?

00:14:01.300 --> 00:14:06.110 align:middle line:84%
But your mind is this incredible
machine that looks at the past

00:14:06.110 --> 00:14:08.060 align:middle line:84%
and says, wow, that
was really traumatic.

00:14:08.060 --> 00:14:10.100 align:middle line:84%
I'm never going to
let that happen again.

00:14:10.100 --> 00:14:13.100 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to lift weights,
or I'm going to get rich.

00:14:13.100 --> 00:14:14.030 align:middle line:90%
Or I'll show them.

00:14:14.030 --> 00:14:15.837 align:middle line:84%
And you do this
whole crazy thing.

00:14:15.837 --> 00:14:17.420 align:middle line:84%
You're only causing
your own suffering

00:14:17.420 --> 00:14:21.080 align:middle line:84%
because it's like trying to jam
a square peg into round hole.

00:14:21.080 --> 00:14:23.220 align:middle line:90%
You can't change the past.

00:14:23.220 --> 00:14:26.030 align:middle line:84%
And yet, if you're out
there, and you're like, well,

00:14:26.030 --> 00:14:28.850 align:middle line:84%
I'll show them that they
shouldn't have mistreated me

00:14:28.850 --> 00:14:30.710 align:middle line:90%
because I'll be famous.

00:14:30.710 --> 00:14:31.520 align:middle line:90%
And I'll be rich.

00:14:31.520 --> 00:14:33.620 align:middle line:90%
And I'll do these things.

00:14:33.620 --> 00:14:34.760 align:middle line:90%
You'll get there.

00:14:34.760 --> 00:14:37.190 align:middle line:84%
And then you'll realize
that those people--

00:14:37.190 --> 00:14:38.592 align:middle line:90%
you don't exist to them.

00:14:38.592 --> 00:14:44.790 align:middle line:84%
So you've lived your whole life
for this inauthentic reason.

00:14:44.790 --> 00:14:46.250 align:middle line:84%
>> As men, especially
in the West,

00:14:46.250 --> 00:14:48.570 align:middle line:84%
we're taught to
suppress our emotions.

00:14:48.570 --> 00:14:49.650 align:middle line:90%
Boys don't cry.

00:14:49.650 --> 00:14:51.690 align:middle line:90%
Men especially don't cry.

00:14:51.690 --> 00:14:54.510 align:middle line:84%
We're taught that emotions
and showing emotion

00:14:54.510 --> 00:14:56.740 align:middle line:90%
is a sign of weakness.

00:14:56.740 --> 00:14:59.290 align:middle line:84%
And so we tend to
suppress those emotions.

00:14:59.290 --> 00:15:01.110 align:middle line:84%
And as a result,
women are much more

00:15:01.110 --> 00:15:04.950 align:middle line:84%
likely to seek help for
emotional difficulties,

00:15:04.950 --> 00:15:07.590 align:middle line:90%
while men are much less likely.

00:15:07.590 --> 00:15:10.590 align:middle line:84%
And so as a result,
men tend to have

00:15:10.590 --> 00:15:15.880 align:middle line:84%
more problems, more diseases
and so on in certain categories.

00:15:15.880 --> 00:15:18.960 align:middle line:84%
What I have seen personally
with emotional baggage

00:15:18.960 --> 00:15:24.900 align:middle line:84%
is that they seem to be the
biggest single underlying cause

00:15:24.900 --> 00:15:28.950 align:middle line:84%
of depression and anxiety
and phobias and panic attacks

00:15:28.950 --> 00:15:34.410 align:middle line:84%
and PTSD and eating disorders
and self-sabotage of all kinds.

00:15:34.410 --> 00:15:38.910 align:middle line:84%
And they also are the
biggest underlying cause

00:15:38.910 --> 00:15:41.940 align:middle line:84%
of the physical pain
that people experience--

00:15:41.940 --> 00:15:45.390 align:middle line:84%
neck pain, migraine headaches,
low back pain, knee pain.

00:15:45.390 --> 00:15:47.160 align:middle line:90%
But other problems too.

00:15:47.160 --> 00:15:52.020 align:middle line:84%
People seek medical help for
many other kinds of conditions.

00:15:52.020 --> 00:15:54.630 align:middle line:84%
And in my experience
over the last 30 years,

00:15:54.630 --> 00:15:56.860 align:middle line:84%
every single one of
those conditions,

00:15:56.860 --> 00:15:59.940 align:middle line:84%
things like infertility and
asthma and digestive disorders,

00:15:59.940 --> 00:16:05.970 align:middle line:84%
and even cancer, all of those
diseases, in my experience,

00:16:05.970 --> 00:16:09.090 align:middle line:84%
always have an underlying
emotional component.

00:16:09.090 --> 00:16:13.450 align:middle line:90%


00:16:13.450 --> 00:16:16.027 align:middle line:84%
>> I always would
say, kind of proudly,

00:16:16.027 --> 00:16:17.610 align:middle line:84%
I was almost killed
in a car accident.

00:16:17.610 --> 00:16:18.410 align:middle line:90%
You know?

00:16:18.410 --> 00:16:21.460 align:middle line:84%
So for about 25
years, until I started

00:16:21.460 --> 00:16:24.430 align:middle line:84%
getting more and more into
compassion and Buddhism

00:16:24.430 --> 00:16:25.640 align:middle line:90%
and things like that.

00:16:25.640 --> 00:16:28.058 align:middle line:84%
And finally, I took
a course, and you had

00:16:28.058 --> 00:16:29.350 align:middle line:90%
to tell the story of your life.

00:16:29.350 --> 00:16:34.260 align:middle line:84%
And someone said, you know,
OK, what happened here?

00:16:34.260 --> 00:16:36.310 align:middle line:84%
And I said I was almost
killed in a car accident.

00:16:36.310 --> 00:16:40.840 align:middle line:84%
And there was a
gentleman who was tasked

00:16:40.840 --> 00:16:43.480 align:middle line:90%
with deconstructing the story.

00:16:43.480 --> 00:16:45.610 align:middle line:84%
And so I say I was almost
killed in a car accident.

00:16:45.610 --> 00:16:47.360 align:middle line:90%
He goes, no, you weren't.

00:16:47.360 --> 00:16:49.360 align:middle line:84%
I said, well, actually,
my femur were shattered.

00:16:49.360 --> 00:16:50.680 align:middle line:90%
My face is blown off my head.

00:16:50.680 --> 00:16:53.020 align:middle line:84%
They didn't notify my
parents because they didn't

00:16:53.020 --> 00:16:54.250 align:middle line:90%
think I was going to live.

00:16:54.250 --> 00:16:56.390 align:middle line:84%
Trust me, I was almost
killed in a car accident.

00:16:56.390 --> 00:16:58.210 align:middle line:90%
He goes, no, you weren't.

00:16:58.210 --> 00:16:59.300 align:middle line:90%
We went back and forth.

00:16:59.300 --> 00:17:02.560 align:middle line:84%
And then, finally, he says
there was a car accident.

00:17:02.560 --> 00:17:04.930 align:middle line:90%
Everything else you added.

00:17:04.930 --> 00:17:06.369 align:middle line:90%
You can't be almost pregnant.

00:17:06.369 --> 00:17:08.050 align:middle line:90%
You can't be almost dead.

00:17:08.050 --> 00:17:09.520 align:middle line:90%
You're either alive or dead.

00:17:09.520 --> 00:17:10.630 align:middle line:90%
There was a car accident.

00:17:10.630 --> 00:17:12.760 align:middle line:90%
So language creates reality.

00:17:12.760 --> 00:17:15.760 align:middle line:84%
The way you choose
to frame your life,

00:17:15.760 --> 00:17:18.250 align:middle line:84%
and you're either the
hero of your story,

00:17:18.250 --> 00:17:19.150 align:middle line:90%
or you're the victim.

00:17:19.150 --> 00:17:22.480 align:middle line:84%
And for those first 25 years,
I realized in that instant

00:17:22.480 --> 00:17:25.119 align:middle line:84%
that I was sucking
people into my drama.

00:17:25.119 --> 00:17:27.849 align:middle line:84%
Trying to get them
to be empathetic.

00:17:27.849 --> 00:17:30.955 align:middle line:84%
And I just made a
conscious choice, like, no.

00:17:30.955 --> 00:17:33.580 align:middle line:84%
So when people ask me now, it's
like, there was a car accident.

00:17:33.580 --> 00:17:42.947 align:middle line:90%


00:17:42.947 --> 00:17:46.420 align:middle line:90%
[SIRENS]

00:17:46.420 --> 00:17:49.060 align:middle line:84%
>> You know, when we look at
trauma and different traumatic

00:17:49.060 --> 00:17:52.270 align:middle line:84%
experiences, I like to
think of it as an empty cup.

00:17:52.270 --> 00:17:53.470 align:middle line:90%
So you've got a water glass.

00:17:53.470 --> 00:17:55.840 align:middle line:84%
And something happens to you
when you're two years old.

00:17:55.840 --> 00:17:57.423 align:middle line:84%
And you pour a little
bit of water in.

00:17:57.423 --> 00:18:00.010 align:middle line:84%
And that's a little
bit of trauma.

00:18:00.010 --> 00:18:04.330 align:middle line:84%
And then five years and
10 years, then a horrible

00:18:04.330 --> 00:18:06.730 align:middle line:90%
experience.

00:18:06.730 --> 00:18:08.290 align:middle line:90%
Eventually, the cup overflows.

00:18:08.290 --> 00:18:10.570 align:middle line:84%
It's too much for
the body to handle.

00:18:10.570 --> 00:18:13.510 align:middle line:84%
That's why some people can
have one traumatic experience.

00:18:13.510 --> 00:18:15.550 align:middle line:90%
And they can change from it.

00:18:15.550 --> 00:18:16.600 align:middle line:90%
They can grow from it.

00:18:16.600 --> 00:18:19.037 align:middle line:84%
There's post-traumatic
growth as a thing.

00:18:19.037 --> 00:18:20.620 align:middle line:84%
And other people, a
soldier comes back

00:18:20.620 --> 00:18:24.220 align:middle line:84%
from war dealing with PTSD,
his nervous system, his body,

00:18:24.220 --> 00:18:28.505 align:middle line:84%
his brain, his spirit is
just completely overwhelmed.

00:18:28.505 --> 00:18:29.880 align:middle line:84%
>> There are two
kinds of trauma.

00:18:29.880 --> 00:18:31.020 align:middle line:90%
There is simple trauma.

00:18:31.020 --> 00:18:32.560 align:middle line:90%
And there's complex trauma.

00:18:32.560 --> 00:18:35.560 align:middle line:84%
And complex trauma is
usually developmental trauma.

00:18:35.560 --> 00:18:38.800 align:middle line:84%
So an example of simple trauma
is somebody is 25 years old.

00:18:38.800 --> 00:18:40.390 align:middle line:90%
They have a terrible car crash.

00:18:40.390 --> 00:18:43.160 align:middle line:84%
And they're in hospital
for a long time.

00:18:43.160 --> 00:18:44.680 align:middle line:84%
It takes them a
great many months

00:18:44.680 --> 00:18:46.210 align:middle line:90%
to regain physical function.

00:18:46.210 --> 00:18:48.940 align:middle line:84%
And this shatters their lives
in some fundamental way.

00:18:48.940 --> 00:18:50.770 align:middle line:90%
That's a simple trauma.

00:18:50.770 --> 00:18:54.640 align:middle line:84%
A complex trauma is one
where there was abuse,

00:18:54.640 --> 00:18:55.780 align:middle line:90%
often as a child.

00:18:55.780 --> 00:18:57.510 align:middle line:84%
And if there's
developed mental trauma

00:18:57.510 --> 00:19:00.010 align:middle line:84%
where you were beaten over and
over and over again, or where

00:19:00.010 --> 00:19:01.940 align:middle line:84%
you were being
neglected, whether you

00:19:01.940 --> 00:19:04.738 align:middle line:84%
were being physically
assaulted, and it was repeated.

00:19:04.738 --> 00:19:06.280 align:middle line:84%
And that's a different
kind of trauma

00:19:06.280 --> 00:19:12.170 align:middle line:84%
because the brain is growing
while that trauma is happening.

00:19:12.170 --> 00:19:14.680 align:middle line:84%
And that information is
being installed at the level

00:19:14.680 --> 00:19:16.450 align:middle line:90%
of circuits in your brain.

00:19:16.450 --> 00:19:20.150 align:middle line:84%
It's not just a thought
or a belief or one event.

00:19:20.150 --> 00:19:22.010 align:middle line:90%
It is crucial.

00:19:22.010 --> 00:19:25.590 align:middle line:84%
It is fundamental to the actual
way your brain wired together.

00:19:25.590 --> 00:19:28.480 align:middle line:84%
For the first two years of
life, the fastest growing brain

00:19:28.480 --> 00:19:30.440 align:middle line:90%
region is the limbic system.

00:19:30.440 --> 00:19:32.350 align:middle line:84%
So the limbic system,
the emotional midbrain,

00:19:32.350 --> 00:19:34.480 align:middle line:84%
is the fastest
growing brain region.

00:19:34.480 --> 00:19:36.940 align:middle line:84%
It's not a part of the
brain that has language,

00:19:36.940 --> 00:19:38.460 align:middle line:90%
but it feels.

00:19:38.460 --> 00:19:39.830 align:middle line:90%
It feels deeply.

00:19:39.830 --> 00:19:42.370 align:middle line:84%
And so if you're
being traumatized

00:19:42.370 --> 00:19:45.250 align:middle line:84%
while that part of
your brain is growing,

00:19:45.250 --> 00:19:50.200 align:middle line:84%
then trauma is woven into
the neural fabric of the way

00:19:50.200 --> 00:19:51.820 align:middle line:90%
your brain structure is.

00:19:51.820 --> 00:19:54.190 align:middle line:84%
And so that kind of
trauma is hard to treat.

00:19:54.190 --> 00:19:56.500 align:middle line:84%
We find in trauma
treatment manuals

00:19:56.500 --> 00:20:00.100 align:middle line:84%
and approaches that simple
trauma is relatively easy,

00:20:00.100 --> 00:20:02.860 align:middle line:84%
but developmental
trauma, complex trauma

00:20:02.860 --> 00:20:04.630 align:middle line:90%
is hard to treat.

00:20:04.630 --> 00:20:07.000 align:middle line:84%
So how does that
person get through it?

00:20:07.000 --> 00:20:11.080 align:middle line:84%
And you can't easily get through
it using cognitive techniques,

00:20:11.080 --> 00:20:13.600 align:middle line:84%
using thought or
language-based therapies.

00:20:13.600 --> 00:20:16.390 align:middle line:84%
I can't sit you
in a chair and say

00:20:16.390 --> 00:20:18.130 align:middle line:84%
you shouldn't feel
that way because it's

00:20:18.130 --> 00:20:20.737 align:middle line:84%
fundamental to the way
your brain functions.

00:20:20.737 --> 00:20:29.330 align:middle line:90%


00:20:29.330 --> 00:20:33.670 align:middle line:84%
>> I grew up in a
really beautiful family.

00:20:33.670 --> 00:20:37.600 align:middle line:84%
My parents would hang out
with this other couple.

00:20:37.600 --> 00:20:40.240 align:middle line:84%
And this man, I was
told to call uncle.

00:20:40.240 --> 00:20:43.260 align:middle line:90%


00:20:43.260 --> 00:20:45.500 align:middle line:90%
We would go to my uncle's house.

00:20:45.500 --> 00:20:48.000 align:middle line:84%
They would all have
some type of party,

00:20:48.000 --> 00:20:49.910 align:middle line:90%
like drink a lot of beer.

00:20:49.910 --> 00:20:51.405 align:middle line:84%
And there were
like rowdy nights.

00:20:51.405 --> 00:20:54.740 align:middle line:90%


00:20:54.740 --> 00:20:56.780 align:middle line:90%
And I would in the back bed.

00:20:56.780 --> 00:20:57.940 align:middle line:90%
And he would come in.

00:20:57.940 --> 00:21:01.330 align:middle line:90%


00:21:01.330 --> 00:21:03.640 align:middle line:84%
It had happened so
many times, and then I

00:21:03.640 --> 00:21:05.860 align:middle line:90%
would fall back asleep.

00:21:05.860 --> 00:21:08.365 align:middle line:84%
I believe that it was happening
before I could even talk.

00:21:08.365 --> 00:21:10.890 align:middle line:90%


00:21:10.890 --> 00:21:14.100 align:middle line:84%
There was a level of
unawareness from my parents

00:21:14.100 --> 00:21:16.380 align:middle line:90%
that it was happening.

00:21:16.380 --> 00:21:19.680 align:middle line:84%
The very first memory that
actually came up for me

00:21:19.680 --> 00:21:22.860 align:middle line:84%
was kind of the bookend
of when it stopped.

00:21:22.860 --> 00:21:26.550 align:middle line:90%


00:21:26.550 --> 00:21:28.200 align:middle line:90%
I must have been five years old.

00:21:28.200 --> 00:21:31.360 align:middle line:84%
And I remember standing
off and being like,

00:21:31.360 --> 00:21:33.190 align:middle line:90%
you're not coming in anymore.

00:21:33.190 --> 00:21:36.510 align:middle line:84%
And I was just like
wanting to stop it.

00:21:36.510 --> 00:21:40.335 align:middle line:84%
And really feeling like I've
got to stand up for myself.

00:21:40.335 --> 00:21:44.030 align:middle line:90%


00:21:44.030 --> 00:21:45.920 align:middle line:84%
And there were times
when I even tried

00:21:45.920 --> 00:21:49.670 align:middle line:90%
to tell my auntie about it.

00:21:49.670 --> 00:21:51.470 align:middle line:90%
And they shut me down.

00:21:51.470 --> 00:21:53.550 align:middle line:84%
I never spoke to
anyone about it.

00:21:53.550 --> 00:21:55.940 align:middle line:84%
And I just got really
bottled down more and more.

00:21:55.940 --> 00:21:59.040 align:middle line:90%


00:21:59.040 --> 00:22:01.140 align:middle line:84%
Obviously, that's
overwhelming for a child,

00:22:01.140 --> 00:22:02.850 align:middle line:84%
so you block it out
and you numb it.

00:22:02.850 --> 00:22:05.160 align:middle line:90%
And you forget about it.

00:22:05.160 --> 00:22:11.130 align:middle line:84%
15 years passed, and when I
hit my late teens, early 20s,

00:22:11.130 --> 00:22:13.842 align:middle line:84%
I went into drugs,
a lot of escapism.

00:22:13.842 --> 00:22:15.300 align:middle line:84%
Didn't want to be
with my thoughts.

00:22:15.300 --> 00:22:17.250 align:middle line:84%
Didn't want to be
with my emotions.

00:22:17.250 --> 00:22:19.050 align:middle line:90%
And really run my body down.

00:22:19.050 --> 00:22:22.030 align:middle line:90%


00:22:22.030 --> 00:22:24.400 align:middle line:90%
I was having anxiety attacks.

00:22:24.400 --> 00:22:25.720 align:middle line:90%
I was really overwhelmed.

00:22:25.720 --> 00:22:30.370 align:middle line:84%
And it got to a peak time where
I started actually smashing

00:22:30.370 --> 00:22:33.010 align:middle line:84%
the window above my
bed to try to escape

00:22:33.010 --> 00:22:34.780 align:middle line:84%
in the middle of
the night thinking

00:22:34.780 --> 00:22:36.820 align:middle line:84%
that there was an
intruder coming in.

00:22:36.820 --> 00:22:39.880 align:middle line:90%


00:22:39.880 --> 00:22:44.200 align:middle line:84%
It was like, what is going
on in my subconscious?

00:22:44.200 --> 00:22:47.470 align:middle line:84%
I didn't start
uncovering my trauma

00:22:47.470 --> 00:22:50.560 align:middle line:84%
until I was probably
19 years old

00:22:50.560 --> 00:22:54.760 align:middle line:84%
after being on a massive
level of escapism on drugs.

00:22:54.760 --> 00:22:57.940 align:middle line:84%
So at that point, not only did
I have to clear the trauma,

00:22:57.940 --> 00:23:00.280 align:middle line:84%
but I had to clear
all of the drug abuse

00:23:00.280 --> 00:23:02.080 align:middle line:90%
that was on top of the trauma.

00:23:02.080 --> 00:23:05.980 align:middle line:84%
So I went into so
many modalities

00:23:05.980 --> 00:23:07.690 align:middle line:84%
to take care of
my physical body,

00:23:07.690 --> 00:23:10.098 align:middle line:90%
such as juicing and cleansing.

00:23:10.098 --> 00:23:12.640 align:middle line:84%
And then, obviously, when you
do that, more emotions come up.

00:23:12.640 --> 00:23:16.300 align:middle line:84%
So I discovered
meditation, yoga.

00:23:16.300 --> 00:23:18.400 align:middle line:90%
I became a Reiki practitioner.

00:23:18.400 --> 00:23:20.740 align:middle line:90%
I studied energy healing.

00:23:20.740 --> 00:23:23.410 align:middle line:84%
I pretty much read every
book that I could find.

00:23:23.410 --> 00:23:27.610 align:middle line:84%
All of these methods allowed
me to drop in and recognize

00:23:27.610 --> 00:23:33.190 align:middle line:84%
who I was and to let go of the
story that was controlling me.

00:23:33.190 --> 00:23:36.010 align:middle line:84%
And when you have a
lot of health issues

00:23:36.010 --> 00:23:38.320 align:middle line:84%
that are caused by
drugs, that's affecting

00:23:38.320 --> 00:23:41.050 align:middle line:84%
your psychology, that's
making you feel sick,

00:23:41.050 --> 00:23:43.310 align:middle line:90%
there's like detox going on.

00:23:43.310 --> 00:23:46.120 align:middle line:84%
And it's very easy for the
mind to identify with that

00:23:46.120 --> 00:23:48.060 align:middle line:90%
and say, oh, that's who I am.

00:23:48.060 --> 00:23:55.100 align:middle line:90%


00:23:55.100 --> 00:23:57.480 align:middle line:84%
I feel like that
earlier time in my life,

00:23:57.480 --> 00:24:01.710 align:middle line:84%
yes, any escapism is
seeking to find love.

00:24:01.710 --> 00:24:03.480 align:middle line:84%
It's seeking to have
that connection.

00:24:03.480 --> 00:24:06.720 align:middle line:84%
It's seeking to feel
held and embraced.

00:24:06.720 --> 00:24:08.970 align:middle line:90%
And so it does give you that.

00:24:08.970 --> 00:24:12.310 align:middle line:84%
And so that's the
beautiful part about it.

00:24:12.310 --> 00:24:16.350 align:middle line:84%
But in that time in my life,
I was getting those feelings,

00:24:16.350 --> 00:24:19.590 align:middle line:84%
but I also wasn't doing
the inner work with them.

00:24:19.590 --> 00:24:23.640 align:middle line:84%
I was combining it with
alcohol and smoking.

00:24:23.640 --> 00:24:27.660 align:middle line:84%
And my mind set wasn't
about looking within.

00:24:27.660 --> 00:24:31.660 align:middle line:84%
It was about partying and
not thinking about it.

00:24:31.660 --> 00:24:35.490 align:middle line:84%
And yeah, it was a hard
process to go through

00:24:35.490 --> 00:24:38.200 align:middle line:84%
to even recognize, like,
oh, did this really happen?

00:24:38.200 --> 00:24:39.540 align:middle line:90%
Like, I haven't remembered this.

00:24:39.540 --> 00:24:42.630 align:middle line:84%
And now, all of a
sudden, but I could feel

00:24:42.630 --> 00:24:44.490 align:middle line:90%
it being released in my body.

00:24:44.490 --> 00:24:47.930 align:middle line:84%
And the intense emotion
that was coming out

00:24:47.930 --> 00:24:51.017 align:middle line:84%
of me when I was healing, I was
like, you can't make this up.

00:24:51.017 --> 00:24:53.100 align:middle line:84%
And I think that's what
happens to a lot of people

00:24:53.100 --> 00:24:55.770 align:middle line:84%
who have blocked out trauma,
especially sexual abuse

00:24:55.770 --> 00:24:57.910 align:middle line:84%
because I work with
a lot of women,

00:24:57.910 --> 00:25:01.080 align:middle line:84%
even men who have had
sexual abuse earlier on.

00:25:01.080 --> 00:25:02.200 align:middle line:90%
And they've numbed it out.

00:25:02.200 --> 00:25:05.480 align:middle line:84%
Oftentimes, they think
they're making it up,

00:25:05.480 --> 00:25:07.890 align:middle line:90%
or how could this be true.

00:25:07.890 --> 00:25:10.358 align:middle line:84%
But if there's emotion
running through your system

00:25:10.358 --> 00:25:12.900 align:middle line:84%
while you're processing it, you
know there's something there.

00:25:12.900 --> 00:25:14.275 align:middle line:84%
>> When something
happens to you,

00:25:14.275 --> 00:25:15.960 align:middle line:84%
and you feel an
emotion coming up,

00:25:15.960 --> 00:25:19.180 align:middle line:84%
that's really a message
from your deep subconscious.

00:25:19.180 --> 00:25:22.620 align:middle line:84%
Now, that message
that's coming up

00:25:22.620 --> 00:25:26.610 align:middle line:84%
is happening not only because of
what's going on in the moment,

00:25:26.610 --> 00:25:29.910 align:middle line:84%
but it's also coming up
because of past experience.

00:25:29.910 --> 00:25:34.500 align:middle line:84%
This phenomenon of trapped
emotions is really universal.

00:25:34.500 --> 00:25:37.950 align:middle line:84%
If you're having any
kind of discomfort,

00:25:37.950 --> 00:25:40.078 align:middle line:84%
that's a sign of
emotional baggage.

00:25:40.078 --> 00:25:42.120 align:middle line:84%
If you're having physical
discomfort in some way,

00:25:42.120 --> 00:25:43.828 align:middle line:84%
there's something that
doesn't feel right

00:25:43.828 --> 00:25:47.910 align:middle line:84%
in your body, 99 times
out of 100 there will be

00:25:47.910 --> 00:25:50.010 align:middle line:90%
some emotional baggage there.

00:25:50.010 --> 00:25:53.640 align:middle line:84%
If you're feeling some kind of
emotional or mental discomfort

00:25:53.640 --> 00:25:56.940 align:middle line:84%
in some way, if your life
isn't working like it should.

00:25:56.940 --> 00:25:59.640 align:middle line:84%
If you keep picking the wrong
kind of person as a mate

00:25:59.640 --> 00:26:01.890 align:middle line:84%
over and over, and you
can't figure out why.

00:26:01.890 --> 00:26:05.820 align:middle line:84%
If you tend to feel certain
emotions that you don't really

00:26:05.820 --> 00:26:07.230 align:middle line:84%
understand, you're
not sure where

00:26:07.230 --> 00:26:10.600 align:middle line:84%
they're coming from, if some
things easily trigger you.

00:26:10.600 --> 00:26:11.430 align:middle line:90%
OK?

00:26:11.430 --> 00:26:14.640 align:middle line:84%
And you can become upset
at the drop of a hat,

00:26:14.640 --> 00:26:18.510 align:middle line:84%
or you find yourself
crying for no reason.

00:26:18.510 --> 00:26:21.360 align:middle line:84%
Or if you are not able to
keep enough money in your bank

00:26:21.360 --> 00:26:22.350 align:middle line:90%
account.

00:26:22.350 --> 00:26:27.570 align:middle line:84%
Or if you just can't seem to
find love, and you're alone.

00:26:27.570 --> 00:26:31.050 align:middle line:84%
Those are all signs
of emotional baggage.

00:26:31.050 --> 00:26:32.730 align:middle line:84%
>> I started working
on the core piece,

00:26:32.730 --> 00:26:35.272 align:middle line:84%
which was like why am I getting
up in the middle of the night

00:26:35.272 --> 00:26:38.310 align:middle line:84%
