some of the stories,

00:27:37.330 --> 00:27:40.270 align:middle line:84%
they can start integrating the
rest of us and living with it.

00:27:40.270 --> 00:27:41.830 align:middle line:84%
And seeing that
there is an upside.

00:27:41.830 --> 00:27:47.140 align:middle line:84%
I mean, that is a very, very,
very, very sensitive subject

00:27:47.140 --> 00:27:49.600 align:middle line:84%
when you present the idea that
perhaps some goodness came

00:27:49.600 --> 00:27:51.790 align:middle line:84%
from the trauma that
you've experienced.

00:27:51.790 --> 00:27:53.470 align:middle line:84%
And people have to
be ready to hear that

00:27:53.470 --> 00:27:54.880 align:middle line:90%
and ready to receive that.

00:27:54.880 --> 00:27:56.410 align:middle line:90%
And then they're open.

00:27:56.410 --> 00:27:59.185 align:middle line:84%
When they start to see there's
something good in this,

00:27:59.185 --> 00:28:00.310 align:middle line:90%
there's a learning in this.

00:28:00.310 --> 00:28:02.050 align:middle line:90%
There's an awareness in this.

00:28:02.050 --> 00:28:04.780 align:middle line:84%
Then they're ready to go back to
the father they haven't spoken

00:28:04.780 --> 00:28:08.020 align:middle line:84%
in 10 years, the mother
they have ostracized out

00:28:08.020 --> 00:28:10.720 align:middle line:84%
of their life, and even the
ones that have passed away

00:28:10.720 --> 00:28:14.170 align:middle line:90%
and to create healing there.

00:28:14.170 --> 00:28:16.600 align:middle line:84%
>> When you take that power
back, and when you say,

00:28:16.600 --> 00:28:19.930 align:middle line:84%
I can let go of that thing
that happened 10 years ago.

00:28:19.930 --> 00:28:22.480 align:middle line:84%
And that's what's crazy
about limiting beliefs,

00:28:22.480 --> 00:28:24.850 align:middle line:90%
our lives, our body, trauma.

00:28:24.850 --> 00:28:27.370 align:middle line:84%
We're not walking around with
what happened this morning

00:28:27.370 --> 00:28:28.240 align:middle line:90%
only.

00:28:28.240 --> 00:28:30.782 align:middle line:84%
We're walking around with what
happened yesterday and the day

00:28:30.782 --> 00:28:33.850 align:middle line:84%
before and really, in the
decades since that have

00:28:33.850 --> 00:28:36.130 align:middle line:90%
made us the people who we are.

00:28:36.130 --> 00:28:38.110 align:middle line:84%
This whole mind-body
concept, right?

00:28:38.110 --> 00:28:40.147 align:middle line:84%
It's like, whoa,
mind-body, it's so new.

00:28:40.147 --> 00:28:42.480 align:middle line:84%
But it's pretty ridiculous
if you think about it, right?

00:28:42.480 --> 00:28:44.272 align:middle line:84%
That we have cut off
ourselves at the head,

00:28:44.272 --> 00:28:46.570 align:middle line:84%
and we're like, OK,
there's the head,

00:28:46.570 --> 00:28:48.080 align:middle line:90%
the things that we think about.

00:28:48.080 --> 00:28:49.410 align:middle line:90%
And then there's the body.

00:28:49.410 --> 00:28:51.910 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, if you think about it,
we have this conscious mind,

00:28:51.910 --> 00:28:53.980 align:middle line:84%
which is where we spend
all of our waking hours.

00:28:53.980 --> 00:28:56.710 align:middle line:84%
The subconscious mind
is the other part of us,

00:28:56.710 --> 00:28:59.350 align:middle line:84%
this vastly
intelligent part of us,

00:28:59.350 --> 00:29:02.500 align:middle line:84%
that is so smart that it
can take the sandwich you

00:29:02.500 --> 00:29:04.390 align:middle line:84%
had for lunch and can
convert some of that

00:29:04.390 --> 00:29:06.940 align:middle line:84%
over into new cardiac muscle
tissue or new nerve cells.

00:29:06.940 --> 00:29:10.090 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it's a level of
intelligence beyond our ability

00:29:10.090 --> 00:29:13.280 align:middle line:84%
to really comprehend at
this point where we are.

00:29:13.280 --> 00:29:17.680 align:middle line:84%
So the conscious mind
is a tiny, tiny part

00:29:17.680 --> 00:29:19.900 align:middle line:90%
of your total intelligence.

00:29:19.900 --> 00:29:22.000 align:middle line:84%
Now, they say that a
single cell in the body

00:29:22.000 --> 00:29:25.330 align:middle line:84%
is equivalent in complexity to
a full size aircraft carrier

00:29:25.330 --> 00:29:28.420 align:middle line:84%
with thousands of people working
onboard at their different jobs

00:29:28.420 --> 00:29:30.212 align:middle line:84%
with jets on the ramp
with their engines

00:29:30.212 --> 00:29:31.420 align:middle line:90%
pulled up, ready to take off.

00:29:31.420 --> 00:29:32.410 align:middle line:90%
That's a single cell.

00:29:32.410 --> 00:29:34.750 align:middle line:84%
And the last estimate was
that the average adult has

00:29:34.750 --> 00:29:36.982 align:middle line:90%
about 137 trillion of those.

00:29:36.982 --> 00:29:39.190 align:middle line:84%
Let me tell you something--
your subconscious mind is

00:29:39.190 --> 00:29:42.370 align:middle line:84%
aware of every single one of
those, down to the DNA level,

00:29:42.370 --> 00:29:44.820 align:middle line:90%
down to the quantum level.

00:29:44.820 --> 00:29:48.400 align:middle line:84%
And so every face you've ever
seen in the crowd, everything

00:29:48.400 --> 00:29:51.370 align:middle line:84%
you've ever eaten or tasted
or touched or smelled,

00:29:51.370 --> 00:29:53.590 align:middle line:84%
the whole history of
your health or disease

00:29:53.590 --> 00:29:57.290 align:middle line:84%
it's all in there in
that subconscious mind.

00:29:57.290 --> 00:30:01.210 align:middle line:84%
So consciously, we are
barely functional, I think.

00:30:01.210 --> 00:30:03.610 align:middle line:84%
We like to think of
ourselves as really smart,

00:30:03.610 --> 00:30:05.440 align:middle line:84%
but the subconscious
mind puts us all

00:30:05.440 --> 00:30:07.630 align:middle line:84%
to shame because it
is so intelligent.

00:30:07.630 --> 00:30:11.440 align:middle line:84%
Now, the problem is, you
see, the conscious mind

00:30:11.440 --> 00:30:17.570 align:middle line:84%
and the subconscious mind need
to agree on certain things.

00:30:17.570 --> 00:30:20.350 align:middle line:84%
For example, let's say
that you would like

00:30:20.350 --> 00:30:23.920 align:middle line:90%
to become wealthy, all right?

00:30:23.920 --> 00:30:24.820 align:middle line:90%
Well, that's fine.

00:30:24.820 --> 00:30:27.060 align:middle line:84%
Consciously you want
to become wealthy.

00:30:27.060 --> 00:30:28.810 align:middle line:84%
And so you want to
move in that direction.

00:30:28.810 --> 00:30:30.520 align:middle line:84%
But if your
subconscious mind has

00:30:30.520 --> 00:30:32.410 align:middle line:84%
learned from the things
that have come in

00:30:32.410 --> 00:30:35.860 align:middle line:84%
as inputs that it's not
OK for you to be wealthy,

00:30:35.860 --> 00:30:37.750 align:middle line:84%
what will happen is
the subconscious mind

00:30:37.750 --> 00:30:38.740 align:middle line:90%
will prevent that.

00:30:38.740 --> 00:30:43.180 align:middle line:84%
Or you may become wealthy,
and then lose that wealth

00:30:43.180 --> 00:30:44.768 align:middle line:84%
and have to regain
it over and over.

00:30:44.768 --> 00:30:46.060 align:middle line:90%
And this applies to everything.

00:30:46.060 --> 00:30:47.680 align:middle line:84%
We actually had
this case once where

00:30:47.680 --> 00:30:49.680 align:middle line:84%
there was a woman who was
trying to lose weight.

00:30:49.680 --> 00:30:51.040 align:middle line:90%
She was very overweight.

00:30:51.040 --> 00:30:53.560 align:middle line:84%
And what had happened
was we finally

00:30:53.560 --> 00:30:56.920 align:middle line:84%
were able to understand
was that she had seen

00:30:56.920 --> 00:30:58.670 align:middle line:90%
what happened with her mother.

00:30:58.670 --> 00:31:01.000 align:middle line:84%
Her mother, when she was
a child, was overweight.

00:31:01.000 --> 00:31:05.290 align:middle line:84%
Went on a diet, lost the
weight, promptly had an affair,

00:31:05.290 --> 00:31:08.200 align:middle line:84%
and destroyed the family,
ended up in divorce.

00:31:08.200 --> 00:31:09.520 align:middle line:90%
Terribly painful.

00:31:09.520 --> 00:31:13.330 align:middle line:84%
So here's this child now,
who's in her 40s and 50s,

00:31:13.330 --> 00:31:16.180 align:middle line:84%
trying to lose weight and
can't because the subconscious

00:31:16.180 --> 00:31:20.680 align:middle line:84%
mind has this idea
that if we lose weight,

00:31:20.680 --> 00:31:21.940 align:middle line:90%
we'll have an affair.

00:31:21.940 --> 00:31:23.170 align:middle line:90%
And our marriage will end.

00:31:23.170 --> 00:31:24.378 align:middle line:90%
And that'll be the end of it.

00:31:24.378 --> 00:31:27.460 align:middle line:84%
And so she was never able to
get to that point, you see?

00:31:27.460 --> 00:31:30.220 align:middle line:84%
And so that emotional
baggage will run us.

00:31:30.220 --> 00:31:33.460 align:middle line:90%


00:31:33.460 --> 00:31:37.090 align:middle line:84%
>> There's a very famous
study called the ACE Study,

00:31:37.090 --> 00:31:38.890 align:middle line:90%
Adverse Childhood Experiences.

00:31:38.890 --> 00:31:41.740 align:middle line:84%
Massive number of people looking
at what happened in childhood.

00:31:41.740 --> 00:31:43.240 align:middle line:84%
And there's an ACE
score, so you can

00:31:43.240 --> 00:31:45.227 align:middle line:84%
go through different
traumatic experiences.

00:31:45.227 --> 00:31:46.060 align:middle line:90%
And you add them up.

00:31:46.060 --> 00:31:48.610 align:middle line:84%
And for the people who have the
highest traumatic experiences

00:31:48.610 --> 00:31:49.820 align:middle line:90%
score, they get one score.

00:31:49.820 --> 00:31:51.903 align:middle line:84%
And if not many things
happen to you in childhood,

00:31:51.903 --> 00:31:52.850 align:middle line:90%
you get another score.

00:31:52.850 --> 00:31:56.130 align:middle line:84%
Now, here's what's crazy about
these this study in particular,

00:31:56.130 --> 00:32:02.080 align:middle line:84%
and it's been repeated
since then, smoking, cancer,

00:32:02.080 --> 00:32:06.220 align:middle line:84%
addiction, directly correlated
with adverse childhood

00:32:06.220 --> 00:32:07.400 align:middle line:90%
experiences.

00:32:07.400 --> 00:32:09.575 align:middle line:84%
So you think to yourself,
what does cancer--

00:32:09.575 --> 00:32:11.200 align:middle line:84%
something happened
to you in childhood,

00:32:11.200 --> 00:32:15.130 align:middle line:84%
and now you're more likely, it's
not like the only determinant,

00:32:15.130 --> 00:32:18.250 align:middle line:84%
but you're more likely to get
cancer statistically because

00:32:18.250 --> 00:32:19.940 align:middle line:90%
of these experiences.

00:32:19.940 --> 00:32:22.240 align:middle line:84%
And I think what's happening
in the body, when we think

00:32:22.240 --> 00:32:24.880 align:middle line:84%
about especially those
tough experiences,

00:32:24.880 --> 00:32:27.410 align:middle line:90%
the environment is unsafe.

00:32:27.410 --> 00:32:28.660 align:middle line:90%
I think about the word safety.

00:32:28.660 --> 00:32:31.540 align:middle line:90%
I use it a lot in tapping.

00:32:31.540 --> 00:32:34.330 align:middle line:90%
Even though I don't feel safe.

00:32:34.330 --> 00:32:36.315 align:middle line:84%
And most people don't
think about that.

00:32:36.315 --> 00:32:38.440 align:middle line:84%
They don't walk around
going do I feel safe or not.

00:32:38.440 --> 00:32:39.910 align:middle line:84%
But if I ask people,
especially who

00:32:39.910 --> 00:32:41.860 align:middle line:84%
have been traumatized
in deep ways,

00:32:41.860 --> 00:32:44.380 align:middle line:90%
do you feel safe in your body?

00:32:44.380 --> 00:32:46.130 align:middle line:90%
They answer, no.

00:32:46.130 --> 00:32:48.430 align:middle line:84%
When they tune in, they go,
and you can do it at home

00:32:48.430 --> 00:32:51.880 align:middle line:84%
right now, you can
close your eyes and go,

00:32:51.880 --> 00:32:54.370 align:middle line:90%
do I feel safe in my body?

00:32:54.370 --> 00:32:56.800 align:middle line:84%
And what that's going to
open you up to is what

00:32:56.800 --> 00:32:59.830 align:middle line:84%
are the parts of you
that have been running

00:32:59.830 --> 00:33:02.620 align:middle line:84%
with that traumatic event,
that have felt anxious,

00:33:02.620 --> 00:33:03.890 align:middle line:90%
that have gripped tight.

00:33:03.890 --> 00:33:04.690 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:33:04.690 --> 00:33:07.240 align:middle line:84%
Because this is what happens
when trauma is created,

00:33:07.240 --> 00:33:09.760 align:middle line:90%
the body goes, uh.

00:33:09.760 --> 00:33:12.550 align:middle line:84%
And all too often,
it doesn't let go.

00:33:12.550 --> 00:33:16.330 align:middle line:84%
And I tell people, if we think
about that holding on tight,

00:33:16.330 --> 00:33:19.030 align:middle line:84%
if I close my fist
right now, and I

00:33:19.030 --> 00:33:21.680 align:middle line:84%
say, OK, I'm going to
squeeze it for five minutes.

00:33:21.680 --> 00:33:22.480 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:33:22.480 --> 00:33:25.035 align:middle line:84%
Five minutes later, this
is going to start to hurt.

00:33:25.035 --> 00:33:26.410 align:middle line:84%
And if I go, well,
you know what,

00:33:26.410 --> 00:33:27.993 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to squeeze
it for two hours.

00:33:27.993 --> 00:33:30.880 align:middle line:84%
Now, this is getting
uncomfortable.

00:33:30.880 --> 00:33:33.460 align:middle line:84%
And it's going to be really
uncomfortable when I open it.

00:33:33.460 --> 00:33:36.340 align:middle line:84%
Now, imagine squeezing
like this for a decade.

00:33:36.340 --> 00:33:37.140 align:middle line:90%
What would happen?

00:33:37.140 --> 00:33:39.223 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I wouldn't be able
to open my hand, right?

00:33:39.223 --> 00:33:40.760 align:middle line:84%
It would probably
get all crippled.

00:33:40.760 --> 00:33:42.220 align:middle line:90%
Blood flow would be affected.

00:33:42.220 --> 00:33:44.230 align:middle line:90%
The growth would be affected.

00:33:44.230 --> 00:33:46.030 align:middle line:84%
If this happened
when I was young,

00:33:46.030 --> 00:33:48.580 align:middle line:84%
who knows how the
fingers actually grow?

00:33:48.580 --> 00:33:52.223 align:middle line:84%
Maybe they stop growing because
they're stuck in this place.

00:33:52.223 --> 00:33:54.640 align:middle line:84%
I think that's what happens
to us emotionally when we have

00:33:54.640 --> 00:33:55.807 align:middle line:90%
these traumatic experiences.

00:33:55.807 --> 00:33:58.150 align:middle line:84%
We're holding on so tight,
and we're walking around

00:33:58.150 --> 00:34:01.240 align:middle line:84%
with this belief about the world
that we got to keep gripping.

00:34:01.240 --> 00:34:02.420 align:middle line:90%
You got to stay safe.

00:34:02.420 --> 00:34:05.215 align:middle line:84%
You can't be open
and vulnerable.

00:34:05.215 --> 00:34:06.840 align:middle line:84%
And that affects the
rest of our lives.

00:34:06.840 --> 00:34:10.130 align:middle line:84%
So then when we-- you talked
about finding in our 20s, 30s,

00:34:10.130 --> 00:34:12.070 align:middle line:84%
40s, whenever it is,
finding that we've

00:34:12.070 --> 00:34:14.949 align:middle line:84%
been gripping like this,
it's a little uncomfortable

00:34:14.949 --> 00:34:17.440 align:middle line:90%
to begin to open that up.

00:34:17.440 --> 00:34:18.429 align:middle line:90%
It can feel unsafe.

00:34:18.429 --> 00:34:19.310 align:middle line:90%
It can be painful.

00:34:19.310 --> 00:34:21.590 align:middle line:84%
They'll go, I don't
want to look there,

00:34:21.590 --> 00:34:25.840 align:middle line:84%
which is why it's great to have
every tool at your disposal--

00:34:25.840 --> 00:34:28.570 align:middle line:84%
tapping, the right practitioner,
or the right therapist,

00:34:28.570 --> 00:34:31.563 align:middle line:84%
especially if it's that
deep traumatic stuff.

00:34:31.563 --> 00:34:32.980 align:middle line:84%
All these new tools
and techniques

00:34:32.980 --> 00:34:34.630 align:middle line:90%
to begin to unfold that.

00:34:34.630 --> 00:34:38.380 align:middle line:84%
To begin to open up that
hand to allow the body

00:34:38.380 --> 00:34:39.733 align:middle line:90%
to feel that it's safe.

00:34:39.733 --> 00:34:41.650 align:middle line:84%
>> Now, when you're
trapped in negative belief

00:34:41.650 --> 00:34:44.830 align:middle line:84%
and you're trying to build
positive neural capacity

00:34:44.830 --> 00:34:48.429 align:middle line:84%
and new beliefs, it's hard
because your brain is used

00:34:48.429 --> 00:34:50.469 align:middle line:90%
to functioning in those ways.

00:34:50.469 --> 00:34:53.110 align:middle line:84%
We know from the work of Nobel
Prize winning Professor Eric

00:34:53.110 --> 00:34:56.500 align:middle line:84%
Kandel that if you pass a
signal through a neural bundle

00:34:56.500 --> 00:34:59.050 align:middle line:84%
repeatedly for an hour,
the number of synapses

00:34:59.050 --> 00:35:02.533 align:middle line:90%
can double in an hour.

00:35:02.533 --> 00:35:03.950 align:middle line:84%
And so what if
you've been passing

00:35:03.950 --> 00:35:05.510 align:middle line:84%
angry thoughts and
resentful thoughts

00:35:05.510 --> 00:35:07.610 align:middle line:84%
or guilty thoughts
or shameful thoughts

00:35:07.610 --> 00:35:10.680 align:middle line:84%
through those circuits for
years and years and years?

00:35:10.680 --> 00:35:13.280 align:middle line:84%
You now have massive
neural bundles dedicated

00:35:13.280 --> 00:35:14.810 align:middle line:90%
to sending those signals.

00:35:14.810 --> 00:35:18.560 align:middle line:84%
And now, you think, gee, you
know, I'm a miserable person.

00:35:18.560 --> 00:35:20.270 align:middle line:90%
I'm horrible to my kids.

00:35:20.270 --> 00:35:21.770 align:middle line:90%
I'm miserable in my job.

00:35:21.770 --> 00:35:24.800 align:middle line:84%
I keep on having
financial disasters.

00:35:24.800 --> 00:35:27.270 align:middle line:84%
I'll go take a weekend
workshop at the Dawson Church,

00:35:27.270 --> 00:35:29.595 align:middle line:84%
you know, Deepak Chopra
or someone like that.

00:35:29.595 --> 00:35:31.970 align:middle line:84%
And so they go to a Tony
Robbins workshop or Joe Dispenza

00:35:31.970 --> 00:35:34.100 align:middle line:84%
workshop or Marianne
Williamson workshop.

00:35:34.100 --> 00:35:35.990 align:middle line:84%
And now, you feel great
after the workshop.

00:35:35.990 --> 00:35:38.570 align:middle line:84%
You're in this temporary
state of euphoria.

00:35:38.570 --> 00:35:39.830 align:middle line:90%
You feel so good.

00:35:39.830 --> 00:35:43.040 align:middle line:84%
But then Monday morning, you're
back in your regular life

00:35:43.040 --> 00:35:45.080 align:middle line:84%
with all the
stimuli that trigger

00:35:45.080 --> 00:35:47.480 align:middle line:84%
the firing of those neural
bundles, which have been

00:35:47.480 --> 00:35:49.100 align:middle line:90%
building for the last 30 years.

00:35:49.100 --> 00:35:51.268 align:middle line:84%
And you revert right
back to the way you are.

00:35:51.268 --> 00:35:53.060 align:middle line:84%
So that's the challenge
of personal growth.

00:35:53.060 --> 00:35:55.610 align:middle line:84%
We have to build that
signaling capacity.

00:35:55.610 --> 00:35:57.740 align:middle line:90%
We have to build that belief.

00:35:57.740 --> 00:36:00.680 align:middle line:84%
We have to build those
positive circuits,

00:36:00.680 --> 00:36:03.680 align:middle line:84%
even before we have
the experience of them.

00:36:03.680 --> 00:36:05.330 align:middle line:84%
>> People only know
what they know.

00:36:05.330 --> 00:36:09.320 align:middle line:84%
So if you're born into a
family that doesn't love,

00:36:09.320 --> 00:36:11.150 align:middle line:84%
then that's what
you think love is.

00:36:11.150 --> 00:36:14.000 align:middle line:84%
And so you look for that
because it's comfortable,

00:36:14.000 --> 00:36:15.290 align:middle line:90%
and it's what you know.

00:36:15.290 --> 00:36:17.540 align:middle line:84%
You don't even know that
a whole new level of love

00:36:17.540 --> 00:36:19.200 align:middle line:90%
is available out there.

00:36:19.200 --> 00:36:21.870 align:middle line:84%
And so you attract people
based on what you expect

00:36:21.870 --> 00:36:24.530 align:middle line:84%
and what you grew up
with a lot of the time.

00:36:24.530 --> 00:36:27.980 align:middle line:84%
It's often very hard
for someone that

00:36:27.980 --> 00:36:33.470 align:middle line:84%
grew up with punishment or abuse
to even recognize that there's

00:36:33.470 --> 00:36:35.220 align:middle line:90%
something better out there.

00:36:35.220 --> 00:36:36.870 align:middle line:84%
They may, like, on
the surface know,

00:36:36.870 --> 00:36:40.510 align:middle line:84%
but on a subconscious
level, as a child,

00:36:40.510 --> 00:36:43.290 align:middle line:84%
especially between the
ages of zero and seven,

00:36:43.290 --> 00:36:44.760 align:middle line:90%
you're looking at your reality.

00:36:44.760 --> 00:36:47.280 align:middle line:84%
You're looking at your
parents, the people that

00:36:47.280 --> 00:36:50.220 align:middle line:90%
taught you as like gospel.

00:36:50.220 --> 00:36:53.670 align:middle line:84%
And that sets up the pathways
to this is what reality is.

00:36:53.670 --> 00:36:55.230 align:middle line:84%
And this is what
you should expect.

00:36:55.230 --> 00:36:56.850 align:middle line:90%
And this is normal.

00:36:56.850 --> 00:36:59.610 align:middle line:84%
And later on, you still
have those patterns,

00:36:59.610 --> 00:37:00.810 align:middle line:90%
so you're looking for that.

00:37:00.810 --> 00:37:02.370 align:middle line:90%
You attract that.

00:37:02.370 --> 00:37:04.980 align:middle line:84%
And then things
get really hectic.

00:37:04.980 --> 00:37:07.890 align:middle line:84%
And you might say, wow, this
isn't really helping me,

00:37:07.890 --> 00:37:10.860 align:middle line:84%
but I keep attracting these
types of people into my life.

00:37:10.860 --> 00:37:15.270 align:middle line:84%
And then, hopefully, you have
some type of support around you

00:37:15.270 --> 00:37:18.450 align:middle line:84%
that can help guide you to
understand that there's so much

00:37:18.450 --> 00:37:22.050 align:middle line:84%
more out there, so much
more available, so much more

00:37:22.050 --> 00:37:25.470 align:middle line:84%
love and caringness that
can come into your life,

00:37:25.470 --> 00:37:28.170 align:middle line:84%
even though you've
never experienced it.

00:37:28.170 --> 00:37:29.520 align:middle line:90%
>> Some people love yoga.

00:37:29.520 --> 00:37:32.760 align:middle line:84%
Some people prefer
Qigong or Tai Chi.

00:37:32.760 --> 00:37:35.310 align:middle line:84%
Some might prefer
martial arts or dance.

00:37:35.310 --> 00:37:36.520 align:middle line:90%
So same thing with therapy.

00:37:36.520 --> 00:37:39.630 align:middle line:84%
Some people respond really well
to cognitive therapies, others

00:37:39.630 --> 00:37:41.730 align:middle line:84%
energy therapies,
others hypnotherapy.

00:37:41.730 --> 00:37:45.450 align:middle line:84%
So you want to play around with
this whole beautiful bundle

00:37:45.450 --> 00:37:46.560 align:middle line:90%
of possibilities.

00:37:46.560 --> 00:37:49.200 align:middle line:84%
And then find the one
that works for you.

00:37:49.200 --> 00:37:51.330 align:middle line:84%
Like someone said to
me once, Tommy Dawson,

00:37:51.330 --> 00:37:52.890 align:middle line:90%
you've done all this research.

00:37:52.890 --> 00:37:55.060 align:middle line:84%
You've looked all these
different therapies.

00:37:55.060 --> 00:37:56.970 align:middle line:90%
Which is the best therapy?

00:37:56.970 --> 00:37:59.820 align:middle line:84%
I said, OK, I'll tell
you the best therapy.

00:37:59.820 --> 00:38:03.865 align:middle line:84%
The best therapy is the
one that works for you.

00:38:03.865 --> 00:38:05.490 align:middle line:84%
Another time someone
said to me, what's

00:38:05.490 --> 00:38:07.040 align:middle line:84%
the very best form
of meditation?

00:38:07.040 --> 00:38:09.420 align:middle line:84%
I said, the best
form of meditation

00:38:09.420 --> 00:38:12.510 align:middle line:90%
is the one you'll do every day.

00:38:12.510 --> 00:38:14.922 align:middle line:84%
So play around in all
these different techniques.

00:38:14.922 --> 00:38:17.130 align:middle line:84%
And then pick the one that
resonates with your energy

00:38:17.130 --> 00:38:20.130 align:middle line:84%
system, with your psyche, with
your history, with your body.

00:38:20.130 --> 00:38:23.980 align:middle line:90%


00:38:23.980 --> 00:38:27.610 align:middle line:84%
>> My beautiful 90-year-old
psychologist and the best

00:38:27.610 --> 00:38:30.580 align:middle line:84%
teacher I've ever had when I've
been going for the toughest

00:38:30.580 --> 00:38:34.810 align:middle line:84%
times said to me, you have
to feel it to heal it.

00:38:34.810 --> 00:38:37.165 align:middle line:84%
And I think there's
real mastery in that.

00:38:37.165 --> 00:38:39.010 align:middle line:84%
In honoring the
feeling of the pain

00:38:39.010 --> 00:38:43.720 align:middle line:84%
rather than covering it with
drugs or alcohol or behavior

00:38:43.720 --> 00:38:46.390 align:middle line:84%
