00:46:46.605 --> 00:46:49.220 align:middle line:90%


00:46:49.220 --> 00:46:53.250 align:middle line:84%
>> EFT stands for emotional
freedom techniques.

00:46:53.250 --> 00:46:54.450 align:middle line:90%
It's also called tapping.

00:46:54.450 --> 00:46:57.420 align:middle line:84%
It has you think about
something that bothers you.

00:46:57.420 --> 00:46:59.730 align:middle line:84%
Now, when you think about
a thing that bothers you,

00:46:59.730 --> 00:47:01.860 align:middle line:84%
you're activating all the
circuits in your brain

00:47:01.860 --> 00:47:03.810 align:middle line:90%
that carry that information.

00:47:03.810 --> 00:47:08.340 align:middle line:84%
So you then have your brain
working in a certain way.

00:47:08.340 --> 00:47:10.500 align:middle line:84%
You have certain
circuits lit up.

00:47:10.500 --> 00:47:12.390 align:middle line:84%
If you think about
things that bother you

00:47:12.390 --> 00:47:14.820 align:middle line:84%
over and over and
over again, you

00:47:14.820 --> 00:47:17.220 align:middle line:84%
make those circuits bigger
and bigger and bigger.

00:47:17.220 --> 00:47:20.190 align:middle line:84%
But if you interrupt that
pattern with something else,

00:47:20.190 --> 00:47:23.250 align:middle line:84%
then you are able to
break that signaling.

00:47:23.250 --> 00:47:25.650 align:middle line:84%
And then your brain no
longer uses that circuit.

00:47:25.650 --> 00:47:28.950 align:middle line:84%
And the something else in the
case of EFT is acupressure.

00:47:28.950 --> 00:47:31.830 align:middle line:84%
There are over 300 meridian
points of the body.

00:47:31.830 --> 00:47:34.870 align:middle line:84%
They're organized into
14 meridian lines.

00:47:34.870 --> 00:47:38.250 align:middle line:84%
And EFT has you apply
acupressure in the form

00:47:38.250 --> 00:47:41.980 align:middle line:84%
of a fingertip tapping,
like this, to about 13

00:47:41.980 --> 00:47:42.780 align:middle line:90%
of those points.

00:47:42.780 --> 00:47:45.390 align:middle line:84%
There are seven in the
brief form of EFT and 13

00:47:45.390 --> 00:47:48.660 align:middle line:84%
in the long form of the FT, as
well as using eye movements.

00:47:48.660 --> 00:47:52.290 align:middle line:84%
And what we see in
people's EEGs and MRIs when

00:47:52.290 --> 00:47:54.540 align:middle line:84%
they do this is that
your first have them

00:47:54.540 --> 00:47:55.738 align:middle line:90%
think about the problem.

00:47:55.738 --> 00:47:57.780 align:middle line:84%
When they think about the
problem about the event

00:47:57.780 --> 00:48:00.750 align:middle line:84%
in their life, about the bomb
blast, about the car crash,

00:48:00.750 --> 00:48:03.660 align:middle line:84%
about the terrible divorce,
whatever it might be,

00:48:03.660 --> 00:48:06.780 align:middle line:84%
you find the emotional
brain is all lit up.

00:48:06.780 --> 00:48:10.260 align:middle line:84%
In an MRI or an EEG, you
see all this activity

00:48:10.260 --> 00:48:11.940 align:middle line:90%
in the emotional midbrain.

00:48:11.940 --> 00:48:14.850 align:middle line:84%
When people start tapping,
it sends a second signal

00:48:14.850 --> 00:48:16.650 align:middle line:90%
to the brain of safety.

00:48:16.650 --> 00:48:19.610 align:middle line:84%
Because if you're being
chased by a tiger,

00:48:19.610 --> 00:48:21.460 align:middle line:90%
you would not be tapping.

00:48:21.460 --> 00:48:24.640 align:middle line:84%
So now, the brain's
getting two inputs.

00:48:24.640 --> 00:48:28.080 align:middle line:84%
It's getting this signal
from your memory saying,

00:48:28.080 --> 00:48:31.380 align:middle line:84%
be stressed, be stressed,
danger, danger, danger, danger.

00:48:31.380 --> 00:48:34.560 align:middle line:84%
And sending a second single,
a somatic signal of soothing

00:48:34.560 --> 00:48:35.970 align:middle line:90%
in the form of tapping.

00:48:35.970 --> 00:48:40.090 align:middle line:84%
And it prioritizes that soothing
signal just the way your mom,

00:48:40.090 --> 00:48:43.240 align:middle line:84%
when you were crying as a baby,
she would stroke your face.

00:48:43.240 --> 00:48:44.950 align:middle line:90%
She would stroke your head.

00:48:44.950 --> 00:48:46.720 align:middle line:90%
She would touch you.

00:48:46.720 --> 00:48:49.300 align:middle line:84%
Our emotional middle
brains understand touch.

00:48:49.300 --> 00:48:51.510 align:middle line:84%
When a friend of
yours is crying,

00:48:51.510 --> 00:48:55.040 align:middle line:84%
you don't explain to them why
they shouldn't feel so bad.

00:48:55.040 --> 00:48:59.340 align:middle line:84%
You put your arm around them,
and touch will soothe them.

00:48:59.340 --> 00:49:01.810 align:middle line:84%
There was a famous psychiatrist
called Joseph Wolpe.

00:49:01.810 --> 00:49:04.270 align:middle line:84%
After World War
II, he was working

00:49:04.270 --> 00:49:06.130 align:middle line:90%
with veterans of World War II.

00:49:06.130 --> 00:49:09.250 align:middle line:84%
And these men, for the most
part men, had shell shock.

00:49:09.250 --> 00:49:12.148 align:middle line:84%
They were dreadfully
affected by the war.

00:49:12.148 --> 00:49:13.690 align:middle line:84%
And he was a good
Freudian therapist.

00:49:13.690 --> 00:49:16.480 align:middle line:84%
So he laid them on a couch
to do the talking cure.

00:49:16.480 --> 00:49:19.540 align:middle line:84%
And said tell me
about Omaha Beach.

00:49:19.540 --> 00:49:22.420 align:middle line:84%
And he came to the
realization after doing this

00:49:22.420 --> 00:49:26.350 align:middle line:84%
with those soldiers, he
said, that kind of therapy

00:49:26.350 --> 00:49:28.390 align:middle line:90%
is not ineffective.

00:49:28.390 --> 00:49:30.150 align:middle line:90%
It's harmful.

00:49:30.150 --> 00:49:34.702 align:middle line:84%
And a later term is
re-traumatizing to remember

00:49:34.702 --> 00:49:36.660 align:middle line:84%
the bad stuff, to remember
the Pit Bull attack,

00:49:36.660 --> 00:49:38.910 align:middle line:84%
remember the car accident,
remember your buddies being

00:49:38.910 --> 00:49:40.540 align:middle line:90%
blown to bits on the beach.

00:49:40.540 --> 00:49:45.820 align:middle line:84%
By replaying that in your mind,
that thought, now stimulating

00:49:45.820 --> 00:49:49.180 align:middle line:84%
that emotion is actually
re-traumatizing you.

00:49:49.180 --> 00:49:52.960 align:middle line:84%
And as you fire those neural
circuits in your brain,

00:49:52.960 --> 00:49:55.430 align:middle line:84%
they wire together bigger
and bigger and bigger.

00:49:55.430 --> 00:49:58.600 align:middle line:84%
So we find, for example,
that stress circuits,

00:49:58.600 --> 00:50:01.445 align:middle line:84%
like the amygdala,
grow in people who have

00:50:01.445 --> 00:50:03.010 align:middle line:90%
been traumatized in that way.

00:50:03.010 --> 00:50:04.990 align:middle line:84%
And learning and
memory circuits,

00:50:04.990 --> 00:50:08.420 align:middle line:84%
like those in the hippocampus,
actually shrink over time.

00:50:08.420 --> 00:50:10.780 align:middle line:84%
So we're doing brain
remodeling with our thoughts.

00:50:10.780 --> 00:50:14.830 align:middle line:84%
Our thoughts aren't just
producing some kind of emotion

00:50:14.830 --> 00:50:16.790 align:middle line:90%
or experience in our minds.

00:50:16.790 --> 00:50:19.680 align:middle line:84%
They're producing neural
tissue in our brains.

00:50:19.680 --> 00:50:21.430 align:middle line:84%
And if you start to
use that neural tissue

00:50:21.430 --> 00:50:24.370 align:middle line:84%
over and over and over again,
then it becomes hard to change.

00:50:24.370 --> 00:50:26.590 align:middle line:84%
So you can't use
cognitive techniques

00:50:26.590 --> 00:50:29.410 align:middle line:84%
for developmental trauma
or preverbal trauma.

00:50:29.410 --> 00:50:30.680 align:middle line:90%
You need energy techniques.

00:50:30.680 --> 00:50:32.055 align:middle line:84%
And we have huge
numbers of them.

00:50:32.055 --> 00:50:35.320 align:middle line:84%
We have acupuncture, which
affects the flows of energy

00:50:35.320 --> 00:50:36.620 align:middle line:90%
in the body's meridians.

00:50:36.620 --> 00:50:38.740 align:middle line:84%
